{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/convex-hull-an-innovative-approach-to-gift-wrap-your-data-899992881efc", "time": 1683004306.954825, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/convex-hull-an-innovative-approach-to-gift-wrap-your-data-899992881efc/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Convex Hull: An Innovative Approach to Gift-Wrap your Data | by Khuyen Tran | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Convex Hull: An Innovative Approach to Gift-Wrap your Data", "description": "Imagine that a rubber band is stretched about the circumference of these nails. If the rubber band is released, it snaps around the points that result in a tight border of the original set. The\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graham_scan", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://github.com/khuyentran1401/Computational-Geometry/blob/master/Graham%20Scan.ipynb", "anchor_text": "Github repository", "paragraph_index": 11}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/khuyen-tran-1401/", "anchor_text": "LinkedIn", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/KhuyenTran16", "anchor_text": "Twitter", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://github.com/khuyentran1401/Data-science", "anchor_text": "this repo", "paragraph_index": 13}], "all_paragraphs": ["Let\u2019s say we have a set of data points.", "Imagine that a rubber band is stretched about the circumference of these nails. If the rubber band is released, it snaps around the points that result in a tight border of the original set.", "The resulting shape is the convex hull, described by the subset of points that touch the border created by the rubber band. The convex hull is a ubiquitous structure in computational geometry. Convex hull has many applications in data science such as:", "The convex hull is also applied to other domains such as data mining, pattern recognition, artificial intelligence, detection of outliers in statistics, and many more. I hope the applications of the convex hull make you excited about this tool. And what is even better? We can create the convex hull for our data! Before moving to the codes, let\u2019s understand how convex hull algorithm works", "Graham\u2019s scan algorithm is a method of computing the convex hull of a definite set of points in the plane.", "The code uses ccw as the determinant for turning left or right. If ccw > 0, then the new point if on the left-hand sides of the previous 2 points. ccw <0 for the left-hand sides and ccw=0 for linear", "You can gain a deeper understanding of the algorithm here.", "Let\u2019s discover how we can utilize Python\u2019s library for our data. It is extremely easy to use convex hull withscipy.spatial.ConvexHull:", "Or turn an image into a convex hull with skimage", "Great! We wrap our data nicely like a gift. Now it is ready to be given as a \u201cgift\u201d to your friends or colleagues. Try this with your data and observe the magic!", "Congratulation! You have just learned a convex hull, an extra tool to work with your data. Data science is not always a linear regression line. Most of the time, you will work with messy data. Thus, knowing what tools are out there will give you the flexibility and power over your data.", "If you are curious about how to code this algorithm with Python, you can find and fork the source code in my Github repository. In my notebook, I explain in detail each piece of code as well as provide the functions you need for the algorithm (counter-clockwise, point class, from points to vector, cross product, etc). Maybe gaining the understanding of this code will give you the confidence to try out with other computation geometry algorithms and create your own module in Python?", "I like to write about basic data science concepts and play with different algorithms and data science tools. You could connect with me on LinkedIn and Twitter.", "Star this repo if you want to check out the codes for all of the articles I have written. Follow me on Medium to stay i